description:
John Scofield is one of the world's most influential jazz guitarists.

Over his four-decade career, John has released 40+ albums as a leader or co-leader, and has played with everyone from Miles Davis to Charles Mingus to Gerry Mulligan to Gary Burton to Phil Lesh to Warren Haynes. That's just a small sampling.

Jarrett Bellini met up with John at The Georgian Terrace hotel in Atlanta to discuss luck, digital music, drugs, sobriety, and more.
